This paper deals with a wireless network, which is a typical topic in the computer science subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the delay-throughput tradeoff, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of cognitive nodes to limit interference is a topic in control theory (cs.SY), and the routing of packets is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to derive the throughput and delay results, which could fall under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
